{
  "text": "Climate change is challenging forest management strategies around the globe [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . In addition to the expected detrimental effects of increasing heat and drought on major physiological processes of forest trees [CITATION_3] , the potential stimulation of mass outbreaks of thermophilic forest pest insects is threatening sustainable forest management [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
